figure_1.caption: Flow of articles through each stage of inclusionary criteria.

claims.sentence:
Methods
Identification of Established Evaluation Criteria
Inclusionary criteria (See Figure 1 for data flow chart) were that the research had to be published in a journal indexed in at least one of the Education Full Text, Education Research Complete, ERIC and PsycINFO databases, with the key term early childhood and at least one of four alphabet-related terms: letter name, letter knowledge, alphabet name, and alphabet knowledge and in the years 2006 to 2018.
